  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Motel Pogir, P-O-G-I-R, M-O-T-E-L.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in Lithuania in 1914.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In [INAUDIBLE], Krekenava, and a couple of months later we were deported [BACKGROUND NOISE] to Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Krekenava is K-R-A-N-O-V-- Krekenava, V-A.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We came-- we, we came back from Russia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We came back in 1921.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was then seven years old, started to go to kindergarten.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My parents, my mom was a housewife, and my father was in the transport business.[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Russia?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Russia, we were in a place by the name called Kazan.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kazan is K-A-Z-A-N.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember very little of then because I was a young little kid, but what I remember is, through Kazan, it goes through a very big river, which the river used to freeze in winter.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The wintertime in, in Russia, the rivers used to freeze.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to existence, for working for an existence, my parents used to send me and a brother of mine, [INAUDIBLE], and we used to chop out a hole in the ice, and the people who used to bring food to the big cities,[BACKGROUND NOISE] the farmers, they used to stop at our place and give it a drink to their-- to their horses.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And for that, they used to give us a couple eggs, a piece of butter, a piece of cheese.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we made from that just a living, a little bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, when we came back, we started to rebuild our house-- which it was burned down-- and reopen the bakery.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I obviously was in, in the years, from school, kindergarten, and then I started to [INAUDIBLE], which is a Hebrew school, Yiddish and Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
